      "kind": "declarations"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When creating an attributed string from a format string, specify this option to apply an attribute to all substituted text. Consider the creation of an attributed string using the format string ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "“Count: %d; Total: %d”",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". After generating the attributed string, the creation method applies the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsreplacementindexattributename",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " attribute to the both integer values in the resulting string. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The value of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsreplacementindexattributename",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " attribute is an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSNumber",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " with the replacement’s position in the format string. The value for the first replacement is 1, for the second replacement is 2, and so on. If you include a positional marker in the format string specifier, the value of the attribute reflects that position, regardless of its actual position in the string. For example, the string ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "“%2@ -- %1@”",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " causes the first argument to have an index value of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "2",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and the second argument to have an index value of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "1",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
